cakes.name: Berries Summer Cupcakes
cakes.description: Summer Berry Cupcakes Deliciously moist and fluffy vanilla cupcakes stuffed with summer berries, and topped with a sweet buttercream frosting!

cakes.name: Brownies Different Flavor
cakes.description: Coffee and dark chocolate are a tried and tested match made in heaven. The Kitchn has delicious coffee brownies recipes in two keys, one for a moist and gooey experience, and the other for an altogether cakier crumb.

cakes.name: Butter Cookies
cakes.description: Butter cookies, also known as Danish biscuits, are cookies originating in Denmark consisting of butter, flour, and sugar. They are similar to shortbread cookies.

cakes.name: Cherry Jelly Cheesecake
cakes.description: cherry blossom cheesecake to celebrate spring's most beautiful flower! A light and smooth cheesecake sits on top of a speculoos cookie crust. The highlight of this cheesecake is the jelly layer.

cakes.name: Chocolate Blueberries Cake
cakes.description: This layered blueberry chocolate cake is very simple to make. It combines fresh flavors in the frosting, both lemon and blueberry. It pairs nicely with the chocolate.

cakes.name: Chocolate Bonbons
cakes.description: A bonbon is a chocolate shell filled with literally anything, usually a flavored ganache, caramel, or jelly.

cakes.name: Chocolate Cookies
cakes.description: A chocolate chip cookie is a drop cookie that features chocolate chips or chocolate morsels as its distinguishing ingredient

cakes.name: Chocolate Cupcake
cakes.description: Chocolate cupcakes are the ultimate party food. These are super moist and bursting with rich, chocolaty flavor — and they're so easy to make.

cakes.name: Chocolate Summer Berries
cakes.description: This silky Dark Milk chocolate bar is topped with strawberries, blueberries, cherries and cookie crunch, the perfect combination of chocolates and tanginess with every bite.

cakes.name: Classic Cheesecake
cakes.description: The perfect classic cheesecake is rich, not too dense, silky smooth, and as creamy as can be.

cakes.name: Cookies Cream Cake
cakes.description: his is soft and buttery white cake filled with cream-filled chocolate sandwich cookies (Oreos!). Top with light and fluffy whipped cream frosting.

cakes.name: Easter Cupcakes
cakes.description: These easy Easter cupcake recipes feature some of spring's best including Cadbury eggs, edible flowers, and other adorable decorations.

cakes.name: Fruit Cake
cakes.description: Fruitcake is a cake made with candied or dried fruit, nuts, and spices, and optionally soaked in spirits. In the United Kingdom, certain rich versions may be iced and decorated. Fruitcakes are usually served in celebration of weddings and Christmas

cakes.name: Isometric chocolate brownies
cakes.description: A brownie is a dense chocolate-flavored baked good traditionally served in small squares. Brownies often contain ingredients like nuts or extracts to give them a distinct flavor other than pure chocolate

cakes.name: Monster Theme Cake
cakes.description: the “Royal Recipe” quest, you can find the recipe for Monster Cake in the Hyrule Castle Library. Gather the necessary ingredients, then find a pot to cook in and bake yourself a Monster Cake.

cakes.name: Muffin Devil Horns
cakes.description: Impishly cute and simple to make, these devil cupcakes are a wickedly delicious treat to serve up at any frightful Halloween party or spooky movie night.

cakes.name: Muffin Ghost
cakes.description: This ghost cake is actually made from a simple batch of cupcakes! Pull-apart cupcake cakes are perfect for parties, as guests can easily enjoy a cupcake

cakes.name: Pumpkin Spice Cupcakes
cakes.description: This is the best pumpkin cake I've ever had and everyone has been raving over it. It's perfectly moist, soft, spiced, and easy to make!
